text: Nuevo México is a corregimiento in Alanje District, Chiriquí Province, Panama. It has a land area of and had a population of 2,101 as of 2010, giving it a population density of . It was created by Law 41 of April 30, 2003. The name of the subdivision references both the country of Mexico and the U.S. state of New Mexico. ==References== Category:Corregimientos of Chiriquí Province
title: Nuevo México, Chiriquí
